AWS Architecture 
The application is containerized using Docker and stored
in Amazon Elastic container Registry. Github actions 
automates CI/CD by building the image and deploying it
to ECS Fargate.

Route53 manages DNS routing to the application load
balancer.
Static or front end part of the game application are
stored in S3, and the data of the application is 
stored in the RDS MariaDB.

Now we are building a fully scalable and serverless
since we are using Fargate. 


Execution flow

Git hub actions
- build a docker image
- pushes to ECR
- now it gets updated in the ECS service

AWS runs Applications

- ECS(Elastic container Service) Fargate starts
 containers
- Application connects to MariaDB
- Application  fetches images from s3

</> Markdown

